1 NOTE There is a story, that tells of Emily's father, along with that of her s
2 CONC ister Minnie. The story tells of how Matilda, Emily's mother and an unk
2 CONC nown man wanted to marry, but his parents were against the match based o
2 CONC n the fact that Matilda was of a lower class. In order to force the iss
2 CONC ue the couple decided that if Matilda was to get pregnant, then there w
2 CONC ould be no question as they would be able to get married. Unfortunately t
2 CONC his plan failed, and Minnie was born, but still no approval to marry. S
2 CONC o they though they would try again, surely with two children, his paren
2 CONC ts would have to agree to the marriage, but again the plan failed, this t
2 CONC ime however the man left the scene, and Matilda was now having to look a
2 CONC fter the two girls, on her own. At this time Matilda moved to Windsor, t
2 CONC he exact reasons are unclear at this time, further investigation is req
2 CONC uired, however once in Windsor, Matilda meets Thomas Archer, and they m
2 CONC arry, Thomas adopts both girls and they take his name. Further investig
2 CONC ation by Rita Smith, granddaughter of Minnie, has thrown up a direct li
2 CONC nk with a lady born in 1780, Rebecca Mitchel, she married a Daniel Arno
2 CONC ld in 1812, and it is therefore thought that the Man, mentioned above, w
2 CONC as in fact a descendant of Rebecca Mitchell, so possibly an Arnold, may b
2 CONC e even a Daniel Arnold. Rita has got this far through a DNA profile, an
2 CONC d it is a firm link to Rebecca Mitchel,, on the basis that Rita's Grand M
2 CONC other and my Grand Mother were full sisters that makes Rebecca my ances
2 CONC tor as well. Rita is investigating this link further, The Arnold Family t
2 CONC ree, as currently known is available from within this tree application.
