1 NOTE Evelyn was born on 3rd October 1919 in Bushey, Watford, Hertfordshire, w
2 CONC here she lived with her parents Emily and Walter, and her sister Margar
2 CONC et, who was born in 1922. She lived in Bushey until spring 1925, follow
2 CONC ing an arguement between Emily and Wlater, where, we suspect, she learn
2 CONC t that he had a wife and family in Connetticut. Emily along with the tw
2 CONC o girls, herself pregnant, traveled to Windsor. Evelyn recalled travell
2 CONC ing into Windsor Central Station, by train, and crossing over the rivie
2 CONC r and Bath Island and seeing buttercups in bloom on the island. In Wind
2 CONC sor they moved around quite a lot, from one room to another, close to t
2 CONC he town centre. in August 1925 they were living in Alma Cottages, South P
2 CONC lace, where her brother Leslie was born.
2 CONT Life was hard, Emily was working, in service, and Evelyn was at school a
2 CONC nd having to look after the two younger children. There were stories, f
2 CONC rom Evelyn, that when they were a little older, and during school holid
2 CONC ays, she would go with friends around teh long walk or over the Brocas, "
2 CONC dragging" the younger children with her, and of her and her friend givi
2 CONC ng Leslie piggy backs .
