3 CONT <b>Sanitation</b>: Buckets served as toilets. Dysentery and lice were c
3 CONC ommon.
3 CONT •
3 CONT <b>Health</b>: Although ships had a designated <b>Surgeon Superintenden
3 CONC t</b> to care for prisoners (a reform after earlier death tolls), disea
3 CONC se outbreaks still occurred. Scurvy, typhoid, and fever were frequent.
3 CONT Simon dying <b>less than two years after arrival</b> suggests he may ha
3 CONC ve <b>suffered illness on board</b> or never recovered from the toll it t
3 CONC ook.<b>🧑‍🏫 3. Daily Life & Routine</b>
