3 CONC ears after arrival — suggesting either <b>lingering illness</b>, <b>har
3 CONC sh labour</b>, or further hardship in the colony.<b>📜 5. Historical Pe
3 CONC rspective</b>
3 CONT Although transportation was often presented as a chance for redemption, i
3 CONC n reality, many transported convicts like Simon were <b>poor, unskilled r
3 CONC ural workers</b>, punished harshly for minor crimes in a society stacke
