1 NOTE Villiers-Bretonneux, was attacked in the early hours of 24th April 1918 b
2 CONC y the German forces, during the day they reinforced there position, but a
2 CONC t 10pm, the same day, Two Australian forces attacked, using a pincer mo
2 CONC vement, for the North and South, "Screamimg and Shouting" forcing the G
2 CONC erman occupation forces to retreat, At this time a number of platoons f
2 CONC rom the 2nd Battalion The Rifles where also involved in the recaputing o
2 CONC f the town, afetr which a number of participants, including Albert Edwa
2 CONC rd Vickers, were awarded the Military Medal.
2 CONT
2 CONT Villiers-Bretonneux, at that time, was an important town for the German
2 CONC s to hold, as it would then give them access to Amiens, which would cut t
2 CONC he supply lines to Paris, which would have handed the victory to German
2 CONC y.
2 CONT
